Flight Sim Company Threatens Reddit Mods Over “Libelous” DRM Posts
Flight sim company FlightSimLabs caused controversy earlier this year after embedding malware in its software to tackle piracy. Now the company is at the center of a new storm after unhappy users on Reddit reported anti-piracy files being installed into Windows systems folders.
